00:26:35,171 --> 00:26:45,399
listening to the source material, find things that you like about the source material. So

347
00:26:45,836 --> 00:26:53,703
some things that you're attracted to because you're going to naturally latch onto those more and probably be able to bring those to your own work better.

348
00:26:53,703 --> 00:27:01,670
Collecting the, you know, isms and, you know, the patterns that you really are attracted to and then adding those to your

349
00:27:01,670 --> 00:27:02,351
palette as well.

